Sentencas: A steady-state and three-dimensional (3-D) model has been established for an intermediate temperature planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Numerical research on carbon activity, fuel utilization, chemical reaction, and temperature distribution for IT single planar SOFC

Sentencas: The model couples charge transfer, mass transfer, momentum transfer, and energy transfer equations.
Titulo: Numerical research on carbon activity, fuel utilization, chemical reaction, and temperature distribution for IT single planar SOFC

Sentencas: Chemical reactions (methane cracking reaction (MCR), Boudouard reaction, methane steam reforming reaction (MSR), and water gas shift reaction (WGSR)) and electrochemical oxidation of H-2 and CO are considered.
Titulo: Numerical research on carbon activity, fuel utilization, chemical reaction, and temperature distribution for IT single planar SOFC

Sentencas: The variations of carbon activity, fuel utilization, and temperature distribution have been discussed with polarization and concentration separately.
Titulo: Numerical research on carbon activity, fuel utilization, chemical reaction, and temperature distribution for IT single planar SOFC

Sentencas: The thermal stress distribution in the positive electrode-electrolyte-negative electrode (P-E-N) structure is also discussed.
Titulo: Numerical research on carbon activity, fuel utilization, chemical reaction, and temperature distribution for IT single planar SOFC

Sentencas: The simulation results agree well with the literature.
Titulo: Numerical research on carbon activity, fuel utilization, chemical reaction, and temperature distribution for IT single planar SOFC
